songs.title: Private Show
songs.lyrics:
[Verse 1]
Silly you, silly me
To let you in and put a move on me
Yeah yeah yeah
Never once asked for love
Always took it for what it's worth, memories

[Pre-Chorus]
See, I don't wanna meet on a lonely street
Where the talk is cheap and the price is sweet
I'm not that girl, I'm not that girl
And you don't want to see the other side of me
So I'ma hit you off and Imma set you free
Before you fall too deep, don't fall too deep

[Chorus]
He don't know
I'ma be the one whose gonna to let him go
Even if he wants to stay, I will let him go
Because all he wants from me is a private show
Ohhh

[Verse 2]
He's all talk, thinks he knows, how this game is supposed to go
For everyone
Still it seems, he can't see
Thinks he's just using me, using me

[Pre-Chorus]
See, I don't wanna meet on a lonely street
Where the talk is cheap and the price is sweet
I'm not that girl, I'm not that girl
And you don't want to see the other side of me
So Imma hit you off and Imma set you free
Before you fall too deep, don't fall too deep

[Chorus]
He don't know
I'ma be the one whose gonna to let him go
Even if he wants to stay, I will let him go
Because all he wants from me is a private show
Ohhh

[Bridge]
He don't know
Maybe if he wasn't such a gigolo, (a nasty hoe)
I would let him stay, instead I let him go
Because all he wants from me is a private show
Ohhh

[Chorus]
He don't know
I'ma be the one who's gonna let him go, I let him go
Private show, oh no no no no
He don't know, Let him go, nasty hoe
Ohhh, private show, he don't know, he don't know
Let him go even if he wants to stay I'll let him go
Because all he wants from me is a private show oh oh oh
He don't know oh oh oh...he don't know
